Lesson Two Reflections


<question> How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository? What value do you think it offers?

<answer> it seems that the staging area is a very useful tool for a scope of and pallet for a collection of materials/files, allowing for an encompassing view before committing

<question>How do the diagrams help you visualize the branch structure?</question>

<answer>...i'm a visual learner and to be able to relate a visual expression to the mapping of repositories is necessary.  And to visualise and comprehend the dynamics of git is essential</answer>

<question> What is the result of merging two branches together? Why do we represent it in the diagram the way we do?</question>

<answer>...merging seems most useful for combining work to the master branch, I imagine the process works the same with non-master branches as far as the auto-merge is concerned.</answer>
